Module iu.util.type
Package edu.iu.type

Interface IuComponentVersion

All Superinterfaces:
Comparable<IuComponentVersion>
public interface IuComponentVersion extends Comparable<IuComponentVersion>
Refers to a component's version.

All components are named and may be referred to by version. Version references are immutable, comparable, and must implement hashCode() and equals(Object). Semantic Versioning must be used to ensure consistency across a variety of components.

A component's implementation version is defined by its component archive. A dependency may require a specific implementation version, or a minimum specification version, to be present on the component's path.

See Also:

  • specificationVersion()

  • Method Details

    • name

      String name()
      Gets the component name.

      The component name should be universally unique, and must be unique within the component's path. The name is part of of the component's version.

      Returns:
      name

    • implementationVersion

      String implementationVersion()
      Gets the implementation version of a component or dependency.

      Must return a value for which SEMANTIC_VERSION_PATTERN.matcher(implementationVersion()).matches() returns true, or null.

      Returns:
      Full Semantic implementation version of the component.
      May be null when referring to a dependency on the component's specification version.
      Must start with major() + '.' + minor() + '.' when non-null.

    • major

      int major()
      Gets the major version number as defined by Semantic Versioning.
      Returns:
      Major version; must be non-negative, should be positive. Non-development applications may reject versions with a major version of 0.

    • minor

      int minor()
      Gets the minor version number as defined by Semantic Versioning.
      Returns:
      Minor version; must be non-negative

    • specificationVersion

      default IuComponentVersion specificationVersion()
      Gets the specification version implied by this version reference.

      The specification version relates to the minor version of the implementation. For example, if the implementation version is 1.2.34-SNAPSHOT, then the specification version is 1.2.

      Returns:
      Specification version implied by this version reference. For an implementation version, the version of the implemented specification is returned. For a specification version, this is returned.
      See Also:
      • major()
      • minor()

    • meets

      default boolean meets(IuComponentVersion requiredVersion)
      Determines if the version implied by this version reference meets the version required by another version reference.

      Note that comparing two version references is not sufficient to determine if a dependency requirement is met since the major versions must be identical in order to consider the requirement met.

      Parameters:
      requiredVersion - Reference to the required version.
      Returns:
      True if the this refers to a version with the same name, and either the same implementation version or same major version and the same or higher minor version as the version reference passed as an argument to the requiredVersion parameter.

    • compareTo

      default int compareTo(IuComponentVersion o)
      Compares two version references.
      • Version references with different names must not return 0; otherwise, the return value enforces natural ordering of the component name.
      • An implementation version compared to another implementation version will return a value that:
        • enforces the numeric order of the major, minor, and patch version numbers
        • enforces the natural order (i.e. +build.12, -SNAPSHOT, -alpha.2, -beta.1) of the combined build and pre-release identifiers
        • is 0 when implementationVersion() strings are identical
      • A specification version compared to another version will return a value that enforces the numeric order of the major and minor version numbers
      • An implementation version is greater than a specification version with matching major and minor version numbers

      Note that comparing two version references is not sufficient to determine if a dependency requirement is met since the major versions must be identical in order to consider the requirement met.

      Note that all versions are case-sensitive.

      Specified by:

    • equals

      boolean equals(Object o)

      Two implementation versions are equal if both name and implementation version are equal. Two specification versions are equal if name(), major(), and minor() are equal.

      An implementation version is never equal to a specification version.

      Note that versions are case-sensitive.
